snippet.textDisplay:
This song holds a unique place in my heart—it always brings me back to her. We were so good together, as if time itself bent to our joy, slipping through our fingers like sand. When she was with me, moments felt fleeting, as if the world was rushing forward in harmony with our laughter.

But now, she’s gone, and time has all but stopped. Each day feels heavier, every second stretching into eternity. The weight of her absence lingers in the silence, in the spaces where she once belonged. Yet, above all, I just hope she is happy. If she is happy, then in some way, I am too.
